[0.004, "o", "\u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[27M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[20;1H; foo = \"None\"  ; sets foo to the string 'None'\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; If you use constants in your value, and these constants belong to a\u001b[K\r\n; dynamically loaded \u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension \u001b[m\u000f(either a PHP \u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension \u001b[m\u000for a Zend extension),\u001b[K\r\n; you may only use these constants *after* the line that loads the extension.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; About this file ;\u001b[K\r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; PHP comes packaged with two INI files. One that is recommended to be used\u001b[K\r\n; in production environments and one that is recommended to be used in\u001b[K\r\n; development environments.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; php.ini-production contains settings which hold security, performance and\u001b[K\r\n; best practices at its core. But please be aware, these settings may break\u001b[K\r\n; compatibility with older or less security-conscious applications. We\u001b[K\r\n; recommending using the production ini in production and testing environments.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; php.ini-development is very similar to its production variant, except it is\u001b[K\r\n; much more verbose when it comes to errors. We recommend using the\u001b[K\r\n; development version only in development environments, as errors shown to\u001b[K\r\n; application users can inadvertently leak otherwise secure information.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; This is the php.ini-production INI file.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; Quick Reference ;\u001b[K\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f66,22           2\u001b[48;12H\u001b[?25h"]
[14.212, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[m\u000f\r\u001b[48;1H\u001b[10X\u001b[1;4Hn your site are atomic, you may increase performance by setting it to \"0\".   \u001b[2;2Hopcache.file_update_protection=2\u001b[39X\r\n\u001b[52X\n; Absolute path used to store shared lockfiles (for *nix only).\u001b[5;2Hopcache.lockfile_path=/tmp\u001b[52X\r\n\u001b[15X\n\u001b[96m[curl]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[10X\u001b[8;3HA default value for the CURLOPT_CAINFO option. This is required to be an\u001b[9;3Habsolute path.\u001b[10;2Hcurl.cainfo =  \r\n\n\u001b[96m[openssl]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[60X\u001b[13;6H location of a Certificate Authority (CA) file on the local filesystem\r\n; to use when verifying the identity of SSL/TLS peers. Most users should\u001b[15;3Hnot specify a value for this directive as PHP will attempt to use the\u001b[8X\u001b[16;3HOS-managed cert stores in its absence. If specified, this value may still\r\n; be overridden on a per-stream basis via the \"cafile\" SSL stream context\u001b[18;3Hoption.\u001b[36X\u001b[19;2Hopenssl.cafile=\u001b[29X\r\n\u001b[47X\n; If openssl.cafile is not specified or if the CA file is not found, the\u001b[22;3Hdirectory pointed to by openssl.capath is searched for a suitable  \u001b[23;3Hcertificate. This value must be a correctly hashed certificate directory. \u001b[24;3HMost users should not specify a value for this directive as PHP will\u001b[7X\r\n; attempt to use the OS-managed cert stores in its absence. If specified,\u001b[26;2H this value may still be overridden on a per-stream basis via the \"capath\"\u001b[27;3HSSL stream context option.\u001b[28;2Hopenssl.capath=   \r\n\u001b[75X\u001b[30;3HThe libctx is an OpenSSL library context. OpenSSL defines a default library\u001b[31;3Hcontext, but PHP OpenSSL also defines its own library context to avoid\r\n; interference with other libraries using OpenSSL and to provide an independent\u001b[33;3Hcontext for each thread in ZTS. Possible values:\u001b[25X\u001b[34;3H \"custom\"  - use a custom library context (default)\u001b[22X\u001b[35;3H \"default\" - use the default OpenSSL library context\u001b[16X\u001b[36;2Hopenssl.libctx=custom\u001b[57X\r\n\n\u001b[96m[ffi]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[72X\u001b[39;3HFFI API restriction. Possible values:\u001b[28X\u001b[40;3H\"preload\" - enabled in CLI scripts and preloaded files (default)\u001b[8X\u001b[41;3H\"false\"   - always disabled\u001b[43X\r\n; \"true\"    - always enabled\u001b[43;2Hffi.enable=preload\u001b[23X\u001b[45;2H List of headers files to preload, wildcard patterns allowed.\u001b[46;2Hffi.preload=\u001b[6X\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f1875,1         Bot\u001b[?112c\u001b[?1002h\u001b[?1006h\r\u001b[A\u001b[?25h"]
